==English==

===verb===
'''nihilate'''

# To encase in a shell of non-being
# Consciousness exists as consciousness by making a nothingness (nihilate) arise between it and the object of which it is consciousness.

===related words===
'''nihilation'''
# That by which consciousness exists

===Word Origin===
This word was created by [[w:Jean-Paul Sartre]] in the original fresh as [[neantir]]. This was translated to English as '''nihilate''' by [[w:Hazel E. Barnes]] in the 1984 version of ''Being and Nothingness'', but was first used in English by [[w:Helmut Kuhn]] in his ''Encounter with Nothingness''.